
@startuml

class Center {
  -name: String
  -address: String
  -rooms: Set<Room>
}

class Room {
  -number: int
  -maxCapacity: int
  -center: Center
}

class Person {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -birthDate: Date
}

class Trainer extends Person {
  -diploma: String
}

class Session {
  -date: Date
  -startTime: Time
  -room: Room
  -type: String (optional)
}

class Participant {
  -person: Person
  -session: Session
}

class SupervisedSession {
  -trainer: Trainer
  -session: Session
}

Center "1" -- "0..*" Room : has
Room "1" -- "1" Center : belongs to
Person "1" -- "0..*" Participant : participates in
Participant "1" -- "1" Session : is part of
Trainer "1" -- "0..*" SupervisedSession : supervises
SupervisedSession "1" -- "1" Session : supervises
Session "1" -- "0..1" Trainer : supervised by (optional)
Session "1" -- "0..*" Participant : has participants

@enduml

---

### Explanation of the Diagram:

- **`Center`**: Represents a fitness center with a unique name, address, and multiple rooms.
- **`Room`**: Each room has a number and max capacity and is located in one center.
- **`Person`**: A generic class representing individuals (members or prospects). It stores first name, last name, and birth date.
- **`Trainer`**: A subclass of `Person`. Trainers have an additional field for their diploma.
- **`Session`**: Represents a session (individual or group) with date, start time, and room. Group sessions also have a type.
- **`Participant`**: A relationship between a person and a session, indicating participation.
- **`SupervisedSession`**: A relationship between a trainer and a session, indicating supervision (only for group sessions).

